Multiple year accruals into the SERP liability were reversed to Undivided Profits since the liability balance came out of earnings for the prior nine years. Accounting entries were reviewed by bank's CPAs and attorneys. Although this liability reversal back to capital is reported as Item 2 in RI-1, it is not really an accounting error or change in accounting principle. But after discussions with FDIC Analyst Sharon Stephens, the recommendation is that Item 2 is the best to show the increase in undivided profits with a detailed explanation.
